    public class Intern
extends java.util.ArrayList<java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>>
    This is the class that is used to store the JSONs from ProteomicsDB in an internal format. These JSONs are structured as an array of data records, where each data record is a set of attribute-value-pairs. This is why the Intern is an ArrayList of LinkedHashMaps: Each entry in the ArrayList corresponds to one data record; each entry in the LinkedHashMap to one attribute-value-pair. ArrayList and LinkedHashMap are used to ensure the correct ordering.
